    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-12-23T00:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-12-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="577"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d577">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/12590: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China (<persName type="from"
                            >Johnson</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-12-23T13:00:00+08:00"
                            >December 23, 1933—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received December 23—11:40 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>927. The Consul at Foochow reports December 22, 11 a.m., that he has received an
                    envelope which had been sent through the regular <pb facs="0654" n="552"
                        xml:id="pg_552"/> mail and censored and chopped by the so-called “6th
                    sub-district Soviet Government of Lienkang district”, Lienkang being north of
                    the Min River entrance. He further stated that according to the publicity organ
                    of the new regime the abolition of extraterritoriality and of the Mixed Court at
                    Kulangsu has been decided on; that a Japanese-owned newspaper claims that the
                    new regime has decided to establish an opium monopoly; and that there are press
                    reports to the effect that all private schools will be instructed to
                    register.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
